{"id":17105,"date":"2024-02-11T19:46:22","date_gmt":"2020-12-11T14:16:22","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/?p=17105"},"modified":"2022-03-31T18:48:50","modified_gmt":"2022-03-31T13:18:50","slug":"balcony-wall-design-ideas","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/home-interiors\/balcony-wall-design-ideas\/","title":{"rendered":"7 Balcony Wall Design Ideas We Like"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p><em>Discover stunning ideas to decorate your front balcony wall<\/em>s<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Any amount of outdoor space is always a blessing for today\u2019s apartment owners. Balconies, no matter what their size, are a perfect, multipurpose space in your home. You can unwind here after a hectic day, spend lazy days reading a book or catching a nap, or chill with friends over a drink. When balconies provide you with such respite, they deserve to be designed with equal care.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Hear us: the size and shape of your balcony don\u2019t matter. There is always ample opportunity to make the space visually and functionally beautiful. Balcony walls carry a lot of design potential. Take a look at these seven front balcony wall design ideas to transform your balcony spaces into something more cosy and beautiful.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Balcony Wall Design With Planters<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Most modern apartments come with smaller balcony spaces. One of the ways to add a bit of charm to the design is by opting for fresh, pastel colours. This balcony is the perfect pleasant spot for a family to enjoy their morning and evening tea. The balcony wall has classic wood panelling and is painted in a fresh shade of pastel green that makes the space look bright and cheerful. The small planters installed on the walls follow the colour scheme of the overall design and decor of the balcony. You can either plant beautiful indoor flowering plants or treat the planters as vases and regularly change the flowers. The bird decor finishes off the design in style.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/12\/11193907\/front-balcony-wall-design-with-planters.jpg\" alt=\"Front balcony wall design with small planters installed, the wall has classic wood paneling that looks bright and cheerful.\" class=\"wp-image-17112\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/12\/11193907\/front-balcony-wall-design-with-planters.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/12\/11193907\/front-balcony-wall-design-with-planters-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/12\/11193907\/front-balcony-wall-design-with-planters-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/12\/11193907\/front-balcony-wall-design-with-planters-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>Add the freshness of flowers to your balcony decor<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n<div class=\"mbgc-slide-caption\"><a href=\"#contactUsModal\" data-toggle=\"modal\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"img-fluid\" alt=\"Lets plan your home interiors together, speak to designers now\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/09\/28124401\/lets-plan-home-interiors-together.jpg \" \/><\/a><\/div>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Modern Vertical Garden<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>One of the simplest ways to decorate your balcony walls is with the use of fresh greens. Homeowners who love plants usually have a mini garden in their balconies or terraces. <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/home-decor\/vertical-garden-design-ideas\/\">Vertical gardens<\/a> are a beautiful way to decorate your balcony walls. Here, the wood-panelled installation makes for a great base and backdrop for the plants. You can either plan climbers in planters on the ground and let them make their way up, or attach planters to the wooden framework. The rest of the decor is kept minimal to let the beautiful garden wall do the talking.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/12\/11193919\/modern-vertical-garden-balcony-wall-design-photo.jpg\" alt=\"Modern balcony wall designed with vertical garden with the support of wooden paneling is balcony wall design ideas.\" class=\"wp-image-17114\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/12\/11193919\/modern-vertical-garden-balcony-wall-design-photo.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/12\/11193919\/modern-vertical-garden-balcony-wall-design-photo-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/12\/11193919\/modern-vertical-garden-balcony-wall-design-photo-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/12\/11193919\/modern-vertical-garden-balcony-wall-design-photo-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>Climbers make for a great balcony wall design<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Explore, more about <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/home-interiors\/balcony-garden-design-ideas\/\">Balcony Garden Design Ideas<\/a><\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Green Boxes For Balcony Wall Design<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>As is evident, there are many different ways to add plants to your balcony wall design in style. An independent unit, whether small or as large as the one used here, can easily be designed and placed against a giant blank wall. Here, the owners have gone for <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/home-decor\/air-purifying-indoor-plants\/\">indoor plants<\/a> and flowering plants in the unit, but you can always think of incorporating different types of decor that can be placed in similar shelves.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/12\/11193913\/green-boxs-for-balcony-front-wall-design.jpg\" alt=\"Plants placed in the green boxes against the balcony wall separately is the balcony front wall design.\" class=\"wp-image-17113\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/12\/11193913\/green-boxs-for-balcony-front-wall-design.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/12\/11193913\/green-boxs-for-balcony-front-wall-design-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/12\/11193913\/green-boxs-for-balcony-front-wall-design-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/12\/11193913\/green-boxs-for-balcony-front-wall-design-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>Place a separate unit with shelves or boxes against your balcony wall for decor<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Statement Decor Piece For Balcony Wall Design<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>If you are keen on doing up one statement wall for balcony design, you can opt for a statement piece of decor to keep the design minimal and classy. For the balcony wall design in question, the owners have opted for grey panels to serve as a backdrop for the minimal and modern wall decor. Neutral colours help in ensuring that the design remains timeless.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/12\/11193901\/decor-piece-for-balcony-wall-design.jpg\" alt=\"Balcony grey wall with a bold piece of decor in a minimal and classy design is the balcony sidewall design.\" class=\"wp-image-17111\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/12\/11193901\/decor-piece-for-balcony-wall-design.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/12\/11193901\/decor-piece-for-balcony-wall-design-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/12\/11193901\/decor-piece-for-balcony-wall-design-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/12\/11193901\/decor-piece-for-balcony-wall-design-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>A bold piece of decor can do the trick for balcony walls<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n<div class=\"mbgc-slide-caption\"><a href=\"#contactUsModal\" data-toggle=\"modal\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"img-fluid\" alt=\"Get a free design consultation from design cafe\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/07\/27144955\/get-free-design-consultation.jpg \" \/><\/a><\/div>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Creative Balcony Wall Decor<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Taking a detour from the use of conventional greens for <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/interior-design\/balcony-design\/\">balcony designs<\/a>, we love how this balcony has an artificial element of green that is beautiful and impactful. The balcony is designed with the use of warm, natural colours and elements that are classic. The wall decor for this small, modern balcony is fresh and minimal. The pretty ceramic plates have an unusual shape which instantly stands out. The small wall lamp on the adjoining wall can help illuminate the decor during the night.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/12\/11193856\/creative-balcony-side-wall-design.jpg\" alt=\"Unusual shape ceramic plates placed on the balcony wall look classic and beautiful designs for balcony wall.\" class=\"wp-image-17110\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/12\/11193856\/creative-balcony-side-wall-design.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/12\/11193856\/creative-balcony-side-wall-design-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/12\/11193856\/creative-balcony-side-wall-design-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/12\/11193856\/creative-balcony-side-wall-design-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>Pretty plates make for prettier wall decor<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Stone Cladding For Balcony Wall Design<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Few things can be as warm as brick walls! Stone cladding on walls gives a nice rustic appeal to a space. The stone cladding design for this wall has created a beautiful, warm corner in the balcony. The red brick walls with the swing chairs, the green of plants and the artificial grass flooring give an illusion of a small piece of a garden being indoors.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/12\/11193849\/brick-walls-for-best-balcony-wall-design.jpg\" alt=\"Balcony with brick wall design created a beautiful backdrop and warm corner with swing chairs in the balcony.\" class=\"wp-image-17109\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/12\/11193849\/brick-walls-for-best-balcony-wall-design.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/12\/11193849\/brick-walls-for-best-balcony-wall-design-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/12\/11193849\/brick-walls-for-best-balcony-wall-design-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/12\/11193849\/brick-walls-for-best-balcony-wall-design-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>Brick walls create a beautiful backdrop and an even better wall design<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Stone Washbasin For Balcony Wall Design<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>A common outdoor wash basin is a great idea since the element becomes much easier to manage. The green wall makes for a beautiful, natural base. The long mirror above the washbasin creates an illusion of even more space in the balcony. The modern yet rustic stone basin is an ingenious way to make use of a balcony wall and a standout feature of the balcony wall design.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/12\/11193925\/stone-wash-basin-balcony-wall-design-idea.jpg\" alt=\"Balcony with stone wash basin and a long mirror against the wall is the modern yet rustic balcony wall design.\" class=\"wp-image-17115\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/12\/11193925\/stone-wash-basin-balcony-wall-design-idea.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/12\/11193925\/stone-wash-basin-balcony-wall-design-idea-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/12\/11193925\/stone-wash-basin-balcony-wall-design-idea-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/12\/11193925\/stone-wash-basin-balcony-wall-design-idea-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>An outdoor wash basin sounds like a great plan for wall design<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n<div class=\"mbgc-slide-caption\"><a href=\"#contactUsModal\" data-toggle=\"modal\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"img-fluid\" alt=\"Looking for a free design consultation\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/07\/28125952\/looking-for-free-design-consultation.jpg \" \/><\/a><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p><em>Giving good thought to balcony wall designs can result in such beautiful outdoor spaces for your apartments. Get in touch with us for customised <\/em><a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/interior-design\/\"><em>interior design<\/em><\/a><em> ideas for your spaces.<\/em><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Also Read:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><li><a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/guides\/how-to-design-your-balcony\/\">How To Design Your Balcony<\/a><\/li><li><a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/home-interiors\/balcony-design-ideas-for-indian-homes\/\">Balcony Design Ideas For Indian Homes<\/a><\/li><\/ul>\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class=\"row blog-form\">\n\t<div class=\"offset-lg-3 col-lg-6 bg-light\">\n<fieldset class=\"field-set\">\n<!-- <legend align=\"left\"> -->\n                    \n    <h3 class=\"widget-title text-dark text-center mb-0\">Looking For Functional Interior Designs?<\/h3>\n  \n \n     <p class=\"text-center text-dark mt-0\"> Get 20% extra space with smart solutions<\/p>\n    <!-- <\/legend> -->\n<form id=\"blogContactUsFormMain\" action=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/get_quote_action.php\" method=\"post\"\n    novalidate=\"novalidate\">\n    <div class=\"form-group\">\n        <input type=\"text\" class=\"form-control\"  name=\"your-name\" placeholder=\"Enter your name*\" \/>\n        <!-- <span class=\"sales-txt-label\" id=\"labeltxt\">Enter your name*<\/span>  -->\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"form-row dc-falg-row\">\n        <!-- <div class=\"form-group col-md-3 guideForm\">\n            <select name=\"your-phone-ext\" id=\"id_select2_example\" class=\"id_select2_example drop-downfield form-dropdown\"\n                onfocus='this.size=5;' onblur='this.size=1;' onchange='this.size=1; this.blur();'\n                data-width=\"100%\" data-minimum-results-for-search=\"Infinity\">\n               \n                <option value=\"+01\"\n                    data-img_src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/10\/06163948\/01.png\">\n                    +01\n                <\/option>\n                <option value=\"+91\"\n                    data-img_src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/10\/06164015\/91.png\"\n